reviews.text:
A meaningful part of local and regional history. The tour was guided and worthwhile, free then to investigate other rooms and grounds. 
It is worth taking a short walk down to the local football ground and park.
Well worth a visit. The gardens are free! The cafe sells the best pot of tea i have ever tasted, for only 2.20.

This is a jewel in the crown of the history of Birmingham. A wonderful building that deserves to be seen by everyone. 
When some people think of Birmingham they think of a city with a thousand trades or the Peaky Blinders. Yet what they should also think about is Aston Hall. 
It's located a stone's throw away from the Villa ground. And within easy access of public transport. 
It won't take long for a quick visit and believe me if you like your local history then this is the place for you.
Gorgeous historical place with a beautiful park around near Aston villa stadium. Worth a visit during a sunny day
Love this place.  Went on a "Who done it night" brilliant plus lovely cafe on site.

Went to listen to the lunchtime concert. It was excellent. Baroque music played on guitars, harp and lute. Vocals were sublime. The museum continues to have other attractions that are worth a visit as is this Victorian building itself. There is a cafe and a shop too.

Great museum in the centre of Birmingham. Basic coffee shop inside but staffed by a lovely girl. Brilliant little section on Egyptians & an interesting temporary exhibit on the sinister aggression of cuteness.
Lots of art works - well restored and looked after. I enjoy take photos of these for classical art memes. Pics attached; have fun captioning then! 😄

Last time I visited the museum must have been at school visits. Not really appreciated then what we truly have. I mostly enjoyed seeing in front of my own eyes was the "Staffordshire hoard" ancient find, hundreds of years old ,magnificent gold,silver and multiple coloured gems. Definitely worth a visit and FREE entry and very helpful and friendly staff.

Lovely place to walk around and check out some art and some history. Some of the exhibits are a bit peculiar, but nevertheless, it's a good time. Great for a rainy day, or feeling like a walk around in a nice and informational museum!

What a fantastic place to visit! It's a massive place and took two and a half hours to look round it.
Lovely Edwardian cafe where we stopped for refreshments.
If this is your kind of thing as it is mine I whole heartedly recommend
Great place! Very interesting with extremely helpful and knowledgeable staff. Would highly recommend a visit.
Lovely families place, friendly atmosphere and always something interesting for every age people. Dogs friendly place and always fresh water for them.

Nice little park and brook surrounded  woodland. Quiet enough to walk your dog and have a short walk. No playground area or kids play areas. The Sarehole Mill National trust tea house is right beside the parking entrance for ease of access.
Just a nice place to go for a bit of history or just a lovely walk with the family what ever the weather.
Great place to visit & take the kids ... visited here on a school trip .. memorable

Lovely , quiet and relaxing atmosphere. Volunteers were very knowledgeable and I learn about many facts regarding Soho house. There were a tall gentleman with grey hair and a lady with a beautiful flower cord over the hair and they tell us different interesting things about Lunar society , about Birmingham in that time. That make me feel proud of the city I live in.The museum looks great and take us in 17th-18th century. In every room were panels where you can read about what that room shown and other few important informations. Museum are laying on ground and first floor where you can reach by using the stairs or using the lift. On the other wing by the house is a Cafe where you can have a ground coffee,tea, cakes, fruits, drinks. You can serve it in or out in the little garden. Also, anyone can enjoying doing some crafts while having a hit/cold drink. There is a little garden and also parking, including for disabled people. Despite that Soho House is located by Soho road which is a very busy road there was so much quietness and peaceful. I couldnt believe I'm just by the main road and the sounds can penetrate the peaceful and relaxing atmosphere here.  I would definitely be back soon and spend more time here.
Very helpful guides and a great place for a small trip

Great to know this gem of a place is on our doorstep.
Great to take young children so they can learn about the City's industrial history.
I was disappointed with the cafe. I'd gone for lunch but there was only hot beverages and biscuits available
An amazing gem and a reminder of how important Birmingham was in the industrial revolution.

Fantastic glimpse into the past. A very interesting insight into the history of Birmingham jewellery trade and what it was like to work at Smith and Pepper. The guided tour with Rupert is a must, as the museum itself is not the most exciting.

Fascinating museum.  I was anticipating more actual jewellery but this is a museum of the workshops and offices.   The guide was so knowledgeable and demonstrated how the jewellers punched out charms etc.   A very interesting place to visit.
Really enjoyed the tour by Debbie. Lots of interesting information in an amazing time warp setting. Well worth a visit.

Fantastic museum that looks like workers only left yesterday. A piece of history paused for all to see.

The guides really bring the museum to life with their knowledge and passion for the era and the jewellery Quarter in general.

You can get a real appreciation for the working conditions that were faced by people working everyday in the workshop.
Very interesting tour round the building with knowledgeable guide. Good way to spend a couple of hours.
Lovely building, really lovely and welcoming people. Very light inside, lots of glass. Dates back to Georgian times. Music was v good ( biased opinion). Particularly liked the final organ piece

A small Cathedral in a large vibrant city. St Philip's is probably one of England's smallest Cathedrals if not the smallest. Originally a Parish Church it became a Cathedral upon the creation of the Diocese of Birmingham.

A lovely welcoming church and a pleasure to look round. I returned for the service of Evening Prayer later in the day.

Needs Sister Act before i get involved in side or on the outside grounds. Just can't get over a boring cathedral with no attitude or any entertainment begging for release any tallent. Needs a shake up badly and urgent holy praise and lots of competitions from around Warickshire to be proud and born again with love something to look forward too a bright happy nation of kind helping hands getting dirty and on the streets for the hardship all around the cathedral begging and remembering it's happening now starvation homeless bring back caring Sister and Priests with gumption in their beliefs. It must be thought from the heart then love will spread and gates of heaven will come alive for all to know we have faith and born again Christians all over the World.
Absolutely one of my favourite places to visit in Birmingham. Gorgeous historic building. Just fabulous. Brilliant acoustics for music and choral performances too. You should definitely visit it!

This is a really good place to head to if you are a reasonably experienced bellringer in Birmingham on a Sunday morning. There are usually 12 ringers ready to ring rounds and call changes right up to surprise royal/max. Warm welcome and good striking.

Nice quiet prayerful place. A decent compromise between the old style rather baroque designs these places were originally fitted out with, and the more modern minimalist style. The building looks a bit lost currently, in a bit of a post industrial wasteland, with new 21st centenary steel and glass beginning to move in, but perhaps (when all the rebuilding is done) the whole will be more harmonious. 
You can pray without distraction, and in safety.
Historic and religiously significant. Worth a visit just to look around but wonderful to enjoy a service here, see the gift shop next door. Home of the Archbishop.
Have been here numerous times over the years and it's still a very impressive cathedral. I find it very peaceful and relaxing when you are out of the hussle and bustle of the city.

This is the Catholic cathedral for Bham...pugin architecture which i love it's small compared to other churches but it has character... St Chad's lady altar on left hand side with v old statue of Mary is special ...lovely latin Mass choir on sundays I think 11am and free organ recitals i believe...yes...a spiritual haven open to all and with a Catholic bookshop next door....a good place to visit for blessings and peace in brum.. St Phillips is nice too in pigeon Park centre of townx
Fantastic cathedral in Birmingham. Its a wonderful house of prayer, open and peaceful. Its a quiet haven in the busy city.
Best
Mooi historisch pand aan de markt. Rondleidingen door het pand worden gegeven door Kring Vrienden van 's-Hertogenbosch.  Te boeken via dagjedenbosch.com. Een aanrader.
Beetje ouderwets.

In dit pand is onder andere de Ombudsman van de gemeente 's-Hertogenbosch gevestigd.
Deze Ombudsman is vaak de laatste strohalm die mensen hebben.
Echter is deze commissie niet van fouten verschoond, fouten die zij zelf toegegeven hebben.

Toch weerhouden die fouten hen er niet van om 'over lijken te gaan' en medewerkers van de gemeente die hun boekje te buiten gaan een handje boven het hoofd te blijven houden ! 

Wat in een onprofessionele, bijna corrupte en incompetente organisatie resulteert.
Men zal zich hier uiteraard 'niet in herkennen' maar dat is altijd het standaard rookgordijn dat snel opgetrokken wordt om zaken binnenkamers te houden.

I think the building dates from around 1903/1904 & even though the building doesn't seem to be no longer a church, because it's a (grade 2?) listed building the red brick & terracotta façade still matches the Magistrates courts opposite it... I've heard it's going to become a hotel now...

Nice hidden gem within the city. Lots of different types of plants you can see both indoors and outdoors.  Good for a family or just taking friends/ dates to. It's worth taking anti histamines before heading to this place to visit though. Cafe coffee is also very nice.

An oasis of tranquility in this city. Gardens were situated over a huge area with few  sections of indoor plants. Special mention for the tea house where we enjoyed some we made scones and tea for once. Will visit again.
Not a bad Botanical Gardens, have been to much bigger but this was still a beautiful gardens. I thought cafe/restaurant was nice as well. Worth a visit

Horrendous ... full of tacky plastic model animals making a lot of screeching noises . We left after having had our senses assaulted.  Pity because we had hoped for a quiet solace in beautiful surroundings. Will be warning our friends not to visit for the remainder of April whilst this ice age event is on.

Absolutely stunning wedding venue!

Attended a friend's civil ceremony here last year - gorgeous grounds, perfect for taking photos in. Plenty of parking, and the gardens are stunning to walk around in.

Always such a pleasure to visit Cannon Hill Park, as there's lots to do with the family. It's such a pleasant place to walk around, feed the birds, play some sport or have a picnic.

Even in the winter months everything is still open and there's still lots to do. I would definitely recommend it for families.

They have a small amusements park with a couple of rides for small children and a cafe at the Mac centre. There is plenty of parking for lots of cars and it's right next to the Birmingham Wildlife Centre. A good day out.

Beautiful park with Lake, children area, cafe, theatre. Very neat and clean garden. 

Riding boat on the Lake extra addition and my children love it. It's just awesome to see lots of swans on the lake and different birds fly around. 
Also one can tour around the park by a small train with very minimum fee. Children love this service. 
Parking facility 

Great place to have fresh air in the busy city life.

Great place to go with family or friends. Good walking trails and 2 parks for children toddlers and young children. Also giant swan boats to paddle in the small lake. 

Also has a little cafe and bar to get some respite. Worth the visit on summer days. Take a picnic if that's your thing.

A great place to come for a walk and some fresh air. Several places to get a coffee, cream tea or an array of other snacks/food. Plenty of entertainment for the kids and adults alike. Parking is £2 all day and the activities (mini golf etc) costs extra but if you wanted to walk or get the bus then there are huge areas of grass that the kids can run around on or are perfect for a picnic. The swan boats are a must!

Beautiful park perfect for a family picnic, park is spacious. With several activities to do such as visiting the MAC building, play tennis, Walk the dog, play area, etc. Lovely and clean! With a short walking trip to Aldi for your nearest convenience.
Love hearing the stories from when our parents we're young,and passing them on to my children. Magical place. Shout out to the people that keep it so nice for us.

Lovely bog park. Paths are marked out and use boards. Can walk around in an hour or so with ease. Nice field with football lines as well.

Just wish it was larger!

Lovely little wild green space in Birmingham with woodlands, open space and a well maintained, pushchair friendly path on duckboards through the bog, so great for an afternoon stroll with the kids. Interesting connection to JRR Tolkien.

An oasis of gentle birdsong - a deep wood where you can quickly forget you're in a very busy city. The wooden pathways around the bog are very helpful and ensure that the woods can be enjoyed even when the terrain is very muddy. The only thing that I would change is to add a bunch of benches - there are next to none, and it's a shame as this would be a great place for a picnic or to sit down and read in.
Great walk and not to long with the little one. I think maybe a bench or 2 to have a seat or food on would be good.

Lovely visit and I have become a member of the RSPB. Lovely walks and a variety of little feathered friends around the area. The Hide is brilliant where you can get as close as possible to many species. Lovely to see the Oyster Catcher sitting on her eggs. Would definitely recommend for all the family.
Nice walk around pool, little visitors centre and hide. Interactive bits on the walk.  Friendly staff. Simple drinks and snacks available. Toilets at red lion farm.
A beautiful place. It's good for the soul. Seen so many beautiful birds, all firsts of mine. Excellent visitor centre and very well managed. CantvwaitC to come again .
Enjoyed the walk around Sandwell Valley Reserve with friends on a beautiful day. Staff are so helpful and maintain the valley do well. Thank you
Great place for walking. Well defined paths and lots of interesting things to see

Beautiful valley with beautiful scenery. It is very spacious and the valley leads you to the barn if you carry on walking straight. On the way, you will spot a red bridge that you can cross to go over the other side. Suitable for runners and even for those who prefer to walk and explore. There's many things you can do here. Photography, jogging etc

Very nice place with children and without children to visit, there is a little farm on one side, there is a horse trekking centre (booking is essential in advance!!!) A little cafe with a public toilet and a nice playground.
I am a regular visitor to this park. It is a spectacular place to walk,cycle or take the air on a scooter as I do. Take the kids to the playground and enjoy a snack in the cafe. Great.

For a local place it’s brilliant for a long walk and it suffices well for a 5K run too. There’s a little farm and a coffee shop with a nice little playground and walking from the park shop and grounds down to the main path takes you along all the fields where the horses are usually put. Cute, but probably not a place to go to 24/7 unless you live locally. Just a nice occasional trip :)
Love this place. In summer there are more activities but for a walk its brilliant. Also you can get to two other parks. Also there is a farm with a small petting zoo.

They doing baby ear piercing here. The staff that work at the jewellery store are really friendly. They ways gave two staff to pierce baby ears as they do both at the same time to prevent added stress to the child which is perfect

Ignite Records is the best record store in the city. A real vinyl cavern that is packed with fairly priced records to suit a wide range of tastes. Rich (the owner) is a real gent, very knowledgeable and accommodating. The store is friendly and welcoming. Important we keep this indie going!
Legendary Birmingham fixture! Great place to get alternative/rock clothing and accessories  in an iconic location in the centre of town for nearly 50 years.

I have been going to Oasis for over 10 years now and every time you go in it is exciting, literally like a kid in a sweet shop. There is always something new and exciting going on. Highly recommend it!

Oasis has lost it appeal and is no longer a fashion markets. It's now full of rude and over priced tattoo parlours and pretentious "clothing shops". Not to mention the shops selling drug paraphernalia. 

Both inside and out the markets are rundown and are stuck in the 1980s and is in need of updating and bring in to this millennium. 
The markets also attracts the wrong kind of people and is a center of anti-social behaviour. I have often seen the police and security patrolling and moving people on. 

The Oasis markets are full of empty stalls and shops, which adds to the rundown feeling.

In conclusion, I would not recommend visting the markets for this reason.
Great location in the Art Gallery. Huge bowl of soup - freshly prepared at an excellent price. Surrounding are fabulous too.
Lovely place but most of the times I went there it was very busy. Soup was delicious and they have a fantastic carrot cake. Didn't like the coffee though.

Edwardian tea room has a quirky and nice atmosphere. However, I found their cream tea overpriced compared to its quality.  The scones were not fresh and the amount of Jam and cream that u get is very tiny.

The service, quality & facilities are still lacking after all these years but oh my, what a wonderful room.
So disappointing that they stop serving food so early, we couldn't have afternoon tea at 4pm one time. That's tea time!
Had a lovely lunch here. The staff were attentive, friendly & helpful. I would recommend this place!
Probably the best place in Selly Oak to get a late night meal. Especially good for students coming home from a night out. Great donner meat. Open till late.
Great place to grab a bite late night

Bit disappointed to see the manager think it's acceptable to just scrape plastic cheese and mayo off a burger when asked without. Not acceptable to take advantage of people just to earn a fiver to buy yourself another ugly shirt. Lactose intolerance is a thing hun x 

poor management = poor staff
Chicken wings are good but chicken stick is just soso
I think they are pleasent and quic

I would say Yorks Cafe is one of the best places in Birmingham for coffee and cake.
They roast their own coffee which is absolutely delicious.  
The decor is quirky with high and low seating, big windows to watch the world go by.
Good menu with options for all dietary needs. 
The Cafe is located on the corner of Stephenson street and Pinfold street,  2 minutes walk from New Street station. 
Highly recommended ☕
Lovely cafe with the beans roasted on-site. Good non-dairy options. Always friendly service! Good food and cakes as well. Convenient near New Street station

Really nice staff and a great selection of food and drinks. Savoury or sweet. This place is popular and you'll know why. For vegans and vegetarians this place has a lot to offer too! Their coffee is really good!

Busy place around the corner from the train station (grand Central). Really really funky decor with loads of seats available - which is tardis- like given how small it looks on the outside. Coffee is well crafted but unfortunately they didn't have filter when I came so didn't try it (only have batch brew). Worth a visit for sure.

actually a v busy place around lunch with a nice atmosphere and the chicken and waffles were so good! Fried chicken was crispy, salty bacon complimented the sweet waffle drizzled in maple syrup🤤 wasn't a cheap brunch but worth it... definitely coming back to try their coffee
Love this place. Always eat here if I'm staying in Birmingham on business. Great food, good price, great service.

Went for a curry here before a show that was on at Arena Birmingham. Good location, close to a few other bars and just a 5-10 minute walk down the canal to the arena. Friendly staff and we were even given Crackers to pull as it's close to Christmas! Can't fault the food but I would recommend booking, we'd booked for 5 which is when it opened and half way through our meal the place was full! Decor needs a bit of a spruce up but still a pleasant atmosphere
Highly recommended this resteraunt, really nice meal, dishes made to order. Very friendly and welcoming staff who make you feel relaxed and at ease. Thank you, I'll be back!
Very tasty and authentic Indian. Really good atmosphere. Reasonable prices.
Terrible food, bad service. Got big attitude when we left and complained. Obvious the appetizers were from Iceland and reheated. . not worth the visit

Great food, friendly service, and they promise to have you served in time for a trip to the Symphony Hall or Hippodrome if you're dining before heading on.

A varied menu, very well priced in a good atmosphere tucked away off the street level.
I am usually a fan of traditional cuisine. Friends brought me here for a party, the food was good, I liked the staff - very friendly and kind!
This looks like a typical French cheap bistrot you would find in Paris, with tables covered with candle wax, it's cute. There isn't much choice in food though.

Called in on Saturday 9th February while shopping in Birmingham with our two grand daughters. We thought it would be a nice way to share in the new year celebrations. The restaurant was nicely decorated for the event. We had not booked and we arrived just before five o’clock. The place was busy with many tables booked but we were given a table as long as we could be finished by 6:15 and were prepared to have our starters along with our main courses. We were quite happy to do this since our parking was going to run our at 6:45 so we wanted a quick meal. The service was excellent and the food delicious. The portions were very generous and if we visit in future we will probably just order one starter and one main course between two people. We had drinks, two starters, four main courses and a large bowl of rice. The total bill was just over £80 which included a 10% service charge. I would have preferred to have paid the tip separately and am not keen on places that automatically add it to the bill but the service was very good and we would have paid this amount anyway. The place was full of families and groups enjoying excellent cuisine and it is an easy place to recommend  and a great place to eat.

Have been going there for years,one of the waiters, Henry(?) Is very friendly and makes you feel welcome, has a lovely manner and good with childcare. The food quality has changed since the other restaurant closed. The serving sizes have gone smaller and taste isn't the same. Unfortunately my  usual hot and sour soup came very sweet!! Despite asking it to be changed, I didn't feel the sweetness was changed! The usual chow mein which never had mushrooms is filled with mushrooms and not mentioned in the menu causing my child to have a mild allergic reaction! Very disappointed!
Not our original destination for dinner but what a suppose. Service very good and staff friendly. Sizzling beef was fantastic.
Efficient service with a bit of good humour thrown in! The food was all lovely, we ordered far too much of course (but took away what was left in a doggy bag). Overall a relaxed and tasty meal.

Good food, and a wide ranging menu of Cantonese food. Relaxing atmosphere, and a very popular place. Efficient service, and the ideal place to go either for a leisurely get together or a pre or post theatre / ballet / concert meal.

The place was full of families and groups enjoying excellent cuisine and it is an easy place to recommend  and a great place to eat.

Despite asking it to be changed, I didn't feel the sweetness was changed! The usual chow mein which never had mushrooms is filled with mushrooms and not mentioned in the menu causing my child to have a mild allergic reaction! Very disappointed!
Not our original destination for dinner but what a suppose. Service very good and staff friendly. Sizzling beef was fantastic.
Efficient service with a bit of good humour thrown in! The food was all lovely, we ordered far too much of course (but took away what was left in a doggy bag). Overall a relaxed and tasty meal.

Good food, and a wide ranging menu of Cantonese food. Relaxing atmosphere, and a very popular place. Efficient service, and the ideal place to go either for a leisurely get together or a pre or post theatre / ballet / concert meal.

Good food, but only 1 out of 4 items ordered were as ordered. 15 minutes wait from ordering to be told something was out of stock, bacon and tomato sandwich brought out instead of sausage and tomato, no mushroom on the the other. Food was good when it arrived but service seemed not quite on the ball. This was a quiet Saturday morning so not sure how it would fare if it was busy

It was a very nice bar. The interior decoration was very homely. The service was really and the staff were really friendly and welcoming. I did not order food, just ordered a latte. I would definitely visit this bar again.
Had a lovely meal and drink here.  Staff attentive and efficient.   Would DEFINITELY recommend.
Lovely café and bar. Beautifully decorated.
Amazing vibes and very friendly staff  . Great food as well . I love it

Hidden away down a side street off Kings Heath High Street met up with family for brunch. It easily accommodated eight of us. Good selection on the menu although we all chose the Full English. Highlights for me the sausage & the tea. It seemed popular with young families on the Sunday we visited. Staff friendly & service was good. Will definitely visit again.

Really love it in here, very tucked away, its a very unique place it has a shop which sells plants and other things for the garden and then a deli too, as well as the cafe. The garden on a sunny day was gorgeous and a great sun trap. Plenty of seating inside and out. We only ordered drinks but I will definitely be ordering food next time as it all looked so good!

Lovely place and plenty of seating. I didn’t love what I ordered- the hash with an egg. Felt it was just mainly potatoes and was expensive. I have heard that they have great food so I will give another try. Great atmosphere though.
Lovely food, inviting place to eat, a haven away from the hub bub. Great friendly service too. Love to hear what the place is like when fuelled with a live band. Good excuse to come back soon!

I love this little place but I do have to mention that the coffee is always served luke warm, plus if you order soya milk they charge extra, and automatically sprinkle with chocolate. I didn't like to ask if the chocolate powder was vegan or not in truth... It's probably better to ask at the counter if someone wants that. They do kindly bring your drinks to you and so I can understand its easier to assume.
Decent, casual and quick place to eat.

We went on a weekend, not sure if that was the reason why it was so quiet. I assume most of their customers are uni students. The Szechuan food was spot on, very "mala" and flavorful. Price wasn't that bad either.
Good service, good food, but can't be paid by card; be able to sort it out, eventually.

We went there because we had a voucher from groupon, so we didn't expect much. Little did we know... The two course meal was more like a four course, the quality of it was great and the service was perfect. We push our limits to eat all of the food because it was too bloody well done to leave it. I would recomend it any time!
I would give 2 stars for the food. But owning to the bad and rude services by an middle aged lady whilst asking for payment, I only gave 1 star. Definitely not worth another visit.

Food very nice, I think this is the best wagamama branch in Birmingham right next to the bullring. Food is generous with ample portions at this branch, staff even gave us complimentary side as the chef's had made an extra accidentally, which was a nice treat, better than throwing it away. Staff are all happy, enthusiastic and respectful to customers. Food arrives quickly and on time. Highly recommend visiting this branch.

Amazing fusion food. All healthy stuff. Would prefer a seat with a back for this price band of restaurant though. There are proper seats three but three place was full.  Will certainly be going back despite this.

A tasty restaurant where you can enjoy Asian and Japanese inspired dishes to warm you any time of day. The staff are always friendly and welcoming and help make the experience even better. There are other Wagamama's in Birmingham but the Bullring unit is by far the best quality in terms of the location and friendliness of the staff.

Great place, amazing food. Helpful and friendly staff. 
Service is pretty quick too.
Reasonable prices. Win, win win.

This was my first time visiting Wagamama and I must say that I was very impressed.  The service was top notch and the food was very tasty and well presented.  I would definitely eat there again no problem.
Amazing restaurant. Small but lovely and you can have takeaway or eat in. You can watch your meal being made by the chef's. A good range and vegetarian and vegan choices

The staff were friendly and the food was good but the establishment is so small. There is maybe like 4/5 tables and there isnt a lot of room for staff to get around. If it was bigger and more comfortable to eat there then I would give it a higher rating.

I wish I could give more than 5 stars for this place. More so for the staff/manager. We sat down and placed our order and watched it being made. When we started eating and tried each others dishes I mentioned I liked the sauce that came with my partners food. The manager was very attentive and brought a portion of the sauce for me to have with my dish. The food was great, nice flavours and presented well.

Lovely food. Nice kind helpful waiters. Very small though but they were accomodating. The sushi is made live and was wonderful. The ramen noodles were brilliant too. It's not the cheapest for what we had but I know they do a much cheaper takeout box If you are interested. Will likely be back.

I had the bento box.  Noodles were lovely, very tasty and a huge portion. The toppings were good too, but lacking in actual meat content (i.e thin piece of chicken with very thick batter, or the stir fried Salmon was more potato than salmon).  Still tasty though!

Lovely little find today. Food menu was minimal so you made your mind up straight away good selection of roasts and vegetarian options. Served warm and by two lovely team members. The guest larger was also very nice & at a fiver a pint reasonably priced. Thank you for a wonderful Sunday lunch.

We went for a team lunch and it was memorable for all the wrong reasons. Malt vinegar (not balsamic) was provided for the bread (which looked like white toasted bread from a packet) , dreadful music. Two colleagues thought their chicken was too pink and the beefburger was cold and not eaten. It is such a pity as it was a good pub. There is a lesson here as we were the only people eating. I am truly embarrassed.

Stylish, good service and casual food done very well. 

 I really enjoyed the meal I had here, although the atmosphere was too loud when the bar was full. Felt like a Yates'. 
Food wise, the Tuna tacos were spot on. Delicious and had a slightly sushi vibe. Beautifully balanced. Cheese burger was perfectly cooked and meaty but messy to eat. Good selection of wine too. 
Overall, worth a visit. It lacks the intimate environment for a date, but certainly enjoyable. 

Note, expect a 12% service charge added to your bill, we got that added on when just two of us dined.
Bottomless brunch was a lovely treat. We ordered salmon off the menu and had a blast. Thanks!

A quirky warm feeling bar just off St Paul's square. Intimate lighting for a meal or cosy drinks. Plays music on a Friday/Saturday night so has a social atmosphere; ideal for pre-drinking a meal at one of the fantastic local restaurants or a night at the Actress and Bishop. There are a few outside benches at the side of the restaurant/bar ideal for a summer drink.

Great food, fantastic service, had the 3 course meal at a very reasonable price. The hazlenut cheesecake is probably the best cheesecake i have ever tasted. The quail starter was fantastic and full of lots of flavour. Would definitely recommend this place to everyone.
Fantastic evening at Opus, excellent food and service. Would recommend every time, for that special evening go to Opus
Excellent menu; food to match. Good understated service. Not cheap but good value. Recommended.
Excellent menu; food to match. Good understated service. Not cheap but good value. Recommended.
Excellent menu; food to match. Good understated service. Not cheap but good value. Recommended.

I ordered from this restaurant and found a METAL SCREW in my lamb.
How on earth that got in there, I have no idea.
I alerted the waiters and they stated they would refund me the cost of the dish (which is below £65.00) and give me a free dish.
I had already ordered enough food and did not want another dish - but the refund simply was not good enough. The screw itself is sharp and thick and would have caused internal damage if I had swallowed it.
I explained this to the 'Chef' who became aggressive and refused to refund me anymore. He does not know where the screw came from.
He then told me to F*** off and leave immediately.

Simply not good enough and dangerous. I would NOT recommend this restaurant. If I could give 0 stars I would.

Where can I start.... I was greeted by the Chef who was very forceful in selling me alcohol even though i don’t drink ..when me and my partner we kindly told him sorry no as when don’t drink any alcohol.He then turned into a raging animal then said me and my husband aren’t welcomed. To me he has a clear-vendetta against people of colour. We decided to leave, bad experience definitely the restaurant did smell sightly of old fish. If you are looking for a decent ambience along with human like exchanges go to Simpson’s or Carter’s and Purnels where the service has been always very good.

My experience at Turners was amazing. The food was above excellent and the service was impeccable. I ordered a bottle of wine for myself and never had to pour my own glass. The attentiveness of the small team was stellar. The food was an absolute master class in how to do fine dining. I had the venison tartar to start which was sumptuous and immaculately presented. I followed that with the fillet and Jersey royal potatoes. I can officially say that the fillet is the best steak I've ever eaten. Perfectly cooked perky pink with zero blood exactly how i liked it. The chocolate tart and peanut butter icecream was a really rich end to the night and just what the doctor ordered. Overall, again, amazing experience. Would recommend you try this place at least once. I know I'll be going back.

Fantastic food and even better service. I loved all the amuses bouches, especially the gruyère profiterole, and the chocolate tart with peanut butter ice cream was unbelievable. Will definitely be going back

Terrible service, an amateur manager who seemed lost and was very rude. We got served after people who came in after us, and his excuse was they were complaining. They just walked in, they didn’t have time to complain, then we didn’t see him the whole night, didn’t even come to the table to say is everything ok, there was 1 waiter who took our order who was very nice, and the supervisor who was very apologetic. The waiter was walking around clueless, saw that we didn’t even have our drinks but didn’t even come to take out order.
Food was average at best but the service really put us off, put us off in general, not just that restaurant, at the end of the night no discount, no apologies, very very bad, at the least we should have got 10 percent off our bill but we received nothing. Would not recommend at all!!

Fantastic place.  Small, probably less than 20 covers situated towards the back of an Indian 'sweet' shop. The food was wonderful.  I went as part of a large group of which only 2 people were Veggie.  I can pretty much say that no one missed having meat. The food was tasty  with loads of variety (I had a Thali which I highly recommend ). I would highly recommend the place even for non-veggies

Lovely, clean, tranquil place to visit for your vegetarian Indian fix if you are into it! As a single lunch break or with the family in the evening - you won't be disappointed.  Quality food as well as service.
Really nice food with a good and varied menu. Also offers takeaway and has an extensive 'deli' counter. Would definitely recommend.
The food is amazing! Friendly relaxed atmosphere, you can take your own drinks if eating in. Everything is vegetarian and also many vegan dishes. Highly recommended.
Cheap and tasty food with friendly staff
Amazing, authentic south Indian food. Love their weekend buffet in particular. Been here so many times. The service could be better though.

Customer service needs to be improved and please serve drinks before the food arrives. There are so many foods that are not available from the menu. Please have items such as tissues available on the table. However, the waiters are friendly and the food are authentic and delicious.

Very poor hygiene, tables and chairs are all dirty, menus are filthy, floor doesn't appear to have ever been cleaned, mats need a vacuum. Cutlery needs a good wash with very hot water to remove the grease.
Felt very uncomfortable here, wouldn't ever go back.

Good place for meals and snacks. They have the South Indian snacks and dishes. Only drawback is they don't accept card, only cash. Luckily there is a nearby cash machine. Quality has slightly gone down compared to few years ago. But not many other options available here in UK.

Friendly staff with good customer service. Food is good but not spicy at all if you prefer spicy food. Price for certain food items were a little too much for small portion. Overall was good place if you like indian food. No onsite parking for the restaurant.
The food was amazing! And the service was also equally great! I would recommend this restaurant to anybody and if I return to this area in the future I'll definitely be returning.
Great place for watching sports if you want to cheer your team on. You friendly and accommodating. You can bet well be back!
Pretty nicely furnished, good vegan food, friendly staff. The toilets are terrible though - there was no soap, and even the dispensers had been taken off the walls.
A fairly calm, clean pub with a range of food options. The bathrooms definitely needed some attention, though.
Foods are terribly awful. It’s way more worthy to buy sandwiches in Tesco rather than having foods here. Never eat here again ever. May be good place for only drinks. But never good for foods.

Excellent food, friendly delivery drivers and polite staff. great place.
They also make me the best coconut rice I've ever had every time and it's not on the menu. 
worth a visit

Been a customer for over 20 years - good vegetarian selection, great food and friendly staff.

I still travel to Selly Oak especially to visit.
Really tasty and good value for money. Also open late for a restuarant/takeaway and worth it if you don't want to resort to fast food. Service was excellent.

Paid for 2 extra poppadoms as everywhere usually gives you two only got 2 so basically charged for free ones! They were both stale AND BENDY! if there messing up somthing so basic like poppadoms and letting them go stale how long is things like meat kept for or stored ??! The delivery driver in the blue corsa C also expects you to walk to the car so he can pass bag out car window!! Shocking start to finish Please dont waste your money  !!
Best curry house in Selly Oak. Friendly service, great food.
Had a lovely meal prior to a show at Symphony Hall. The food was delicious and the wine very nice. The serving staff were delightful, very friendly, attentive and helpful. Highly recommended.
First time staying here, but had a lovely stay. Staff very friendly and helpful. Rooms clean and tidy. Pool area just relaxing. Just a great stay.

The hotel is amazing but lack of parking brings it down slightly with no suggestions. Luckily we found a great secure and reliable car park one street away called Car Park 22. Regardless it was a fairly positive stay apart from that.
Stayed here over Christmas, lovely hotel with everything you need. Pool area was clean and relaxing. Bar area was cosy. Rooms well a good size and catered well for a family.

It has been a while since I visited last and they have done a wonderful refurbishment. The place looks fresher and the feel is more modern. Staff are still friendly, rooms are still comfortable and the breakfast is still excellent.

Amazing food. Food was served very quickly, but didn't compromise on quality. This place is a hidden gem. Staff are very friendly, Jack is a very hospitable host. Almost feel like not sharing this place so I can keep it to myself.
One of the most popular Chinese restaurant in Selly Oak, comes with fast delivery/order and student-friendly pricing. Recommended.

Amazing combo deals. £5.50 for any meat including duck or prawns and a selection of sauces with any rice/noodles. Huge portions and generous with meat. Very filling. Nice place to sit in and eat on a student budget.
The customer service was a bit off but it was the end of the day it is understandable. The food is really tasty though.
I worked there one day as a delivery driver a girl  who taking orders she is very sweet
Cheap food, good pancakes. Lots of board games available to play. A legendary location for Birmingham students
Fantastic cafe, just like the ones back home in Walsall. Really nice sausage sandwiches, perfect with a cup of tea
Awful food (cheap ingredients/products), filthy, mediocre service, bad décor and disgusting toilets that have no hand wash!
Not a bad place for breakfast with a nice full english and pancake selection. A little grimy though.
Fantastic family owned (17 years) place to get grub, although it may be changing ownership/closing down soon.

It's a Nicholson's pub, quite easy to miss (you need to duck under an archway with a doorway somewhat hidden to the side that drops you down a staircase to a cellar dwelling.

Met up with some family friends for dinner who recommended this place; we were shown to a table deep inside the premises and decided to opt for pies. The meal was good, beer fine (a mixture of Nicholson's own and some other guest beers) and service excellent.  I decided to try a pudding, cheesecake with a generous dollop of cream.

The total bill for 4 people for meals plus plenty of beers came to under £100 - excellent value for what we had. Will definitely return if I'm in the area.
Wonderful place. Fabulous premises, great food and brilliant staff. Couldn't have been better and cannot wait to go there again.

Lovely little hideaway with a great atmosphere and eclectic clientele. A good range of reasonably priced wines and ales to suit any taste. Bar staff are polite and helpful. Wheelchair access through a lift

Always a fun place to dine out. Standard pub F&B. Great atmosphere on Friday night. Very busy. Unusual decor too. Reservations recommended. Private parties can take over a larger than usual space so you've been warned! ;-). Good service and happy waiting staff. Thank you. See you again.

An unusual themed bar with so much potential. Great gin selection but if it isn't on the menu,, they can't do cocktails. Interesting Roman meets Egyptian theme but in need of a clean. Thick dust on the light shade over our table, cobwebs on the curtains. A real shame as it could be a great location.

They have a 15 minute, live concert every weekday at noon, where they play different types of music on the bells. Sometimes traditional music, sometimes modern music. You can hear it from all over campus!
Iconic Iowa State clock tower
Iconic Iowa State landmark
Great place to take wedding photos.

The iconic clock/bell tower that's featured in pretty much any photo collection of Iowa State University.  There's always a small musical performance at noon as well as the quarter hour chimes during normal business hours.  The recent construction of a short wall on Union Dr. (just south of the campanile) has become a really popular spot for people to take photos while visiting ISU.
Had a lovely meal prior to a show at Symphony Hall. The food was delicious and the wine very nice. The serving staff were delightful, very friendly, attentive and helpful. Highly recommended.
First time staying here, but had a lovely stay. Staff very friendly and helpful. Rooms clean and tidy. Pool area just relaxing. Just a great stay.

The hotel is amazing but lack of parking brings it down slightly with no suggestions. Luckily we found a great secure and reliable car park one street away called Car Park 22. Regardless it was a fairly positive stay apart from that.
Stayed here over Christmas, lovely hotel with everything you need. Pool area was clean and relaxing. Bar area was cosy. Rooms well a good size and catered well for a family.

It has been a while since I visited last and they have done a wonderful refurbishment. The place looks fresher and the feel is more modern. Staff are still friendly, rooms are still comfortable and the breakfast is still excellent.

Another hotel favourite. 

Rooms are lovely. Roll top baths and comfortable beds. 

Breakfast is amazing. Eggs Benedict and Royale are the best.

Definitely recommend. 

Great location for city centre and jewellery quarter nightlife.
Amazing from start to finish.  Fantastic room, comfortable bed and huge roll top bath.  Great package deal for dinner B&B on A Friday night.
Nice Hotel, interesting history....  good place to stay in the centre of the city. Our room nice but bathroom tired although clean and serviceable...  👍🏻

My husbans and I went to Hotel du Vin & Bistro for our anniversary lunch - Sunday roast. This is a fusion restaurant (English & French cuisine) you can expect lovely twist on your typical roast. I had french style steak with chips and my hubby beef roast for mains  - both we very tasty. We were in rush so we took lemon pie with us - this was also pleasant. Service was good although it could be quicker.

Enjoyed lunch and spa treatment package. The lunch was delicious with plenty of food, massages were lovely and relaxing. The atmosphere in the restaurant was a bit dull and spa facilities limited. However everyone was very welcoming and friendly.

I used to go there to learn meditation. Everyone was very welcoming and friendly. You don't have to be a Buddhist to go. But if you want to learn more about this sect of Buddhism, then this is the ideal place to come. They've always got various things going and everyone is welcome. Nice for an introduction and more if you wish.
A tranquil place, an excellent sound bath, from Edan Sound.
A place where you are welcome

I often come here for meetings.  Parking for disabled drivers on drive and unrestricted street parking for able bodied drivers. Internal steps with reasonable handrails. Wheelchair lift but not usually anybody around who knows how to make it work at the times when I visit.
Friendly people and amazing meditation classes

I came here to buy food from the deli shop, which is staffed by volunteers, so open limited hours. People were friendly and helpful. I'm not Jewish; I used to buy Jewish food occasionally from the shop on Pershore Road which closed a few years ago. This shop has a range of foodstuffs I haven't seen anywhere else in Birmingham and I look forward to trying them.
An enjoyable experience.
It was closed. Non of the phones answering. Hard to find.
Beautiful liturgy
Lovely environment, lovely building and amazing people!
Important place of worship for the hindu community. I visited the temple over 30 years ago.
Old Radha Krishna Mandir ....one of the first in the UK.  Beautiful place with many childhood memories.
Lovely temple. Difficult to find parking around pick times.
very nice hindu temple I am very happy to see such a nice place here in UK
Jai shree Ram
